00:23:25.580 --> 00:23:26.890 align:middle line:90%
of the human being.

00:23:26.890 --> 00:23:30.440 align:middle line:84%
They're not talking about the
development of consciousness.

00:23:30.440 --> 00:23:33.980 align:middle line:84%
They're not even talking about
the prevention of disease

00:23:33.980 --> 00:23:36.360 align:middle line:90%
and the promotion of health.

00:23:36.360 --> 00:23:38.860 align:middle line:84%
They're only talking
about treating disease

00:23:38.860 --> 00:23:42.470 align:middle line:84%
through a medical system
that is very invasive, very

00:23:42.470 --> 00:23:45.380 align:middle line:84%
expensive, and often
too late, you know,

00:23:45.380 --> 00:23:47.610 align:middle line:90%
once the disease has begun.

00:23:47.610 --> 00:23:50.020 align:middle line:84%
So we started a
political party, which

00:23:50.020 --> 00:23:52.960 align:middle line:90%
grew to be quite significant.

00:23:52.960 --> 00:23:58.620 align:middle line:84%
And the idea was to promote
prevention-oriented solutions

00:23:58.620 --> 00:24:01.460 align:middle line:84%
and consciousness-based
solutions,

00:24:01.460 --> 00:24:05.580 align:middle line:84%
understanding that people
always act on the basis of who

00:24:05.580 --> 00:24:07.660 align:middle line:84%
they are, on the basis
of the development

00:24:07.660 --> 00:24:09.500 align:middle line:90%
of their consciousness.

00:24:09.500 --> 00:24:12.170 align:middle line:84%
And if you can promote the
development of consciousness,

00:24:12.170 --> 00:24:15.880 align:middle line:84%
unfold the full human being,
develop the total brain,

00:24:15.880 --> 00:24:19.330 align:middle line:84%
in the schools, for
example, you can

00:24:19.330 --> 00:24:22.890 align:middle line:84%
create an entirely different
society and an entirely

00:24:22.890 --> 00:24:24.370 align:middle line:90%
different world.

00:24:24.370 --> 00:24:27.280 align:middle line:84%
So the purpose of third
parties in the United States

00:24:27.280 --> 00:24:31.680 align:middle line:84%
is not actually to win,
although that would be nice.

00:24:31.680 --> 00:24:33.360 align:middle line:90%
Because you can't win, really.

00:24:33.360 --> 00:24:38.250 align:middle line:84%
The finances and the system is
stacked so heavily against you.

00:24:38.250 --> 00:24:42.360 align:middle line:84%
But the idea of third
parties where they do succeed

00:24:42.360 --> 00:24:48.200 align:middle line:84%
is in injecting new ideas into
the political dialogue, ideas

00:24:48.200 --> 00:24:52.060 align:middle line:84%
that if they're timely
will take root and start

00:24:52.060 --> 00:24:54.250 align:middle line:90%
to spread like a wildfire.

00:24:54.250 --> 00:24:57.170 align:middle line:84%
And we were able to really
disseminate some new ideas

00:24:57.170 --> 00:24:58.800 align:middle line:84%
and to create some
really important

00:24:58.800 --> 00:25:00.250 align:middle line:84%
new solutions which
have never been

00:25:00.250 --> 00:25:02.320 align:middle line:90%
discussed politically before.

00:25:02.320 --> 00:25:05.245 align:middle line:84%
So that's the reason for
a political agitation,

00:25:05.245 --> 00:25:07.620 align:middle line:90%
a political activism.

00:25:07.620 --> 00:25:10.920 align:middle line:84%
But ultimately,
the solutions have

00:25:10.920 --> 00:25:13.490 align:middle line:90%
to come from deeper than that.

00:25:13.490 --> 00:25:16.470 align:middle line:84%
Politics is a little bit
of a superficial approach.

00:25:16.470 --> 00:25:20.270 align:middle line:84%
You really need to introduce
change from within.

00:25:20.270 --> 00:25:23.190 align:middle line:90%
Change always begins within.

00:25:23.190 --> 00:25:23.890 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:25:23.890 --> 00:25:28.000 align:middle line:84%
So it's more the 97% of the
population that doesn't have

00:25:28.000 --> 00:25:32.570 align:middle line:84%
the supposedly authority
that could make

00:25:32.570 --> 00:25:33.973 align:middle line:90%
a difference in this world?

00:25:33.973 --> 00:25:35.935 align:middle line:84%
-Exactly.
-Us.

00:25:35.935 --> 00:25:38.930 align:middle line:84%
Us, yes, the
grassroots, so to speak,

00:25:38.930 --> 00:25:43.140 align:middle line:84%
the average person,
really all of us,

00:25:43.140 --> 00:25:45.430 align:middle line:90%
have to be part of the solution.

00:25:45.430 --> 00:25:48.230 align:middle line:84%
You could even elect, in
principle, an enlightened

00:25:48.230 --> 00:25:50.700 align:middle line:84%
government, and the
government would

00:25:50.700 --> 00:25:54.380 align:middle line:84%
be somewhat limited in
what it can really do.

00:25:54.380 --> 00:25:56.150 align:middle line:84%
Because ultimately,
the government

00:25:56.150 --> 00:25:59.630 align:middle line:84%
can try to impose laws
and try to control

00:25:59.630 --> 00:26:04.020 align:middle line:84%
behavior from the outside in
through fear of punishment,

00:26:04.020 --> 00:26:05.230 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:26:05.230 --> 00:26:08.920 align:middle line:84%
But you know, fear of
punishment doesn't really work.

00:26:08.920 --> 00:26:11.310 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the United States
has the toughest penal code

00:26:11.310 --> 00:26:12.660 align:middle line:90%
in the world, in a sense.

00:26:12.660 --> 00:26:16.030 align:middle line:90%
Capital punishment is used.

00:26:16.030 --> 00:26:19.540 align:middle line:84%
But it still has a very,
very high murder rate.

00:26:19.540 --> 00:26:22.020 align:middle line:84%
So the death penalty
doesn't even work.

00:26:22.020 --> 00:26:24.860 align:middle line:84%
Really, activity
comes from within.

00:26:24.860 --> 00:26:29.490 align:middle line:84%
And to change an individual
from within to take

00:26:29.490 --> 00:26:33.480 align:middle line:84%
the light of life, the
light of consciousness,

00:26:33.480 --> 00:26:36.580 align:middle line:84%
the amount of
awareness or conscious

00:26:36.580 --> 00:26:38.670 align:middle line:84%
that we have, and
turn it up and up

00:26:38.670 --> 00:26:42.570 align:middle line:84%
and up from inside like a
light bulb becoming brighter.

00:26:42.570 --> 00:26:44.880 align:middle line:84%
That will lead to
more enlightened, more

00:26:44.880 --> 00:26:47.860 align:middle line:90%
luminous thinking and behavior.

00:26:47.860 --> 00:26:49.940 align:middle line:84%
So we have to start
with education.

00:26:49.940 --> 00:26:54.930 align:middle line:84%
Education should-- it's supposed
to-- develop human potential.

00:26:54.930 --> 00:26:56.220 align:middle line:90%
And today it really doesn't.

00:26:56.220 --> 00:26:58.650 align:middle line:84%
It provides some information,
some useful facts,

00:26:58.650 --> 00:27:00.410 align:middle line:90%
some useful skills.

00:27:00.410 --> 00:27:03.270 align:middle line:10%
But unfortunately, in
terms of developing

00:27:03.270 --> 00:27:09.850 align:middle line:10%
the enormous potential
of life and of the brain,

00:27:09.850 --> 00:27:13.080 align:middle line:10%
education completely
fails to do that.

00:27:13.080 --> 00:27:16.950 align:middle line:10%
And that's why fundamental
education reform is necessary.

00:27:16.950 --> 00:27:18.210 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't mean new classrooms.

00:27:18.210 --> 00:27:19.810 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't mean computers.

00:27:19.810 --> 00:27:24.220 align:middle line:84%
It means powerful,
natural techniques

00:27:24.220 --> 00:27:26.910 align:middle line:90%
to develop the brain.

00:27:26.910 --> 00:27:29.040 align:middle line:84%
Even if those
techniques are ancient,

00:27:29.040 --> 00:27:31.770 align:middle line:84%
even if they may
come from the East,

00:27:31.770 --> 00:27:34.150 align:middle line:84%
that doesn't mean
they're religious.

00:27:34.150 --> 00:27:37.500 align:middle line:84%
Gravity was discovered
in England by Newton,

00:27:37.500 --> 00:27:39.330 align:middle line:90%
doesn't make gravity English.

00:27:39.330 --> 00:27:41.120 align:middle line:84%
Relativity was
discovered by a German.

00:27:41.120 --> 00:27:44.800 align:middle line:84%
Einstein doesn't make
relativity German.

00:27:44.800 --> 00:27:47.810 align:middle line:84%
Meditation was ultimately
derived and developed

00:27:47.810 --> 00:27:49.680 align:middle line:84%
in the ancient
Vedic culture, and

00:27:49.680 --> 00:27:52.370 align:middle line:84%
the whole system of
yoga, for example,

00:27:52.370 --> 00:27:53.890 align:middle line:90%
doesn't make it Indian.

00:27:53.890 --> 00:27:59.140 align:middle line:84%
It's universal knowledge,
and we all need to use it.

00:27:59.140 --> 00:28:02.230 align:middle line:84%
Obviously you love children,
and you're passionate about it,

00:28:02.230 --> 00:28:05.270 align:middle line:84%
and you see that they're a
big part of the solution.

00:28:05.270 --> 00:28:08.260 align:middle line:84%
How do we develop
as human beings?

00:28:08.260 --> 00:28:09.640 align:middle line:90%
How does our brain evolve?

00:28:09.640 --> 00:28:11.730 align:middle line:84%
And when are these
principles especially

00:28:11.730 --> 00:28:13.780 align:middle line:90%
important to teach to children?

00:28:13.780 --> 00:28:17.360 align:middle line:84%
And even what should parents
teach to their own children

00:28:17.360 --> 00:28:18.560 align:middle line:90%
and at what age?

00:28:18.560 --> 00:28:20.180 align:middle line:84%
Because it's very
earlier on, isn't it?

00:28:20.180 --> 00:28:22.720 align:middle line:84%
Before six years old,
or what are the--?

00:28:22.720 --> 00:28:26.095 align:middle line:84%
It's true, to some degree,
a lot of what we absorb

00:28:26.095 --> 00:28:28.690 align:middle line:84%
and what shapes us
is from our parents.

00:28:28.690 --> 00:28:30.760 align:middle line:90%
It's from a very early age.

00:28:30.760 --> 00:28:34.930 align:middle line:84%
I think really the best thing--
best thing-- a parent can do

00:28:34.930 --> 00:28:41.500 align:middle line:84%
is themselves to be happy
and balanced and evolving.

00:28:41.500 --> 00:28:46.570 align:middle line:84%
But by the age of 10, a
child can sit down and close

00:28:46.570 --> 00:28:50.710 align:middle line:84%
the eyes, surprising as it
may be, within a few minutes,

00:28:50.710 --> 00:28:53.550 align:middle line:84%
with proper guidance,
can experience

00:28:53.550 --> 00:28:58.350 align:middle line:84%
unbounded, universal, immortal
consciousness, just as you can,

00:28:58.350 --> 00:29:00.030 align:middle line:90%
just as I can.

00:29:00.030 --> 00:29:01.210 align:middle line:90%
It's that simple.

00:29:01.210 --> 00:29:02.740 align:middle line:90%
It's that natural.

00:29:02.740 --> 00:29:05.750 align:middle line:84%
And over the
centuries, meditation

00:29:05.750 --> 00:29:09.860 align:middle line:84%
has become misunderstood,
difficult, complicated,

00:29:09.860 --> 00:29:11.710 align:middle line:84%
something for the
recluse, something

00:29:11.710 --> 00:29:15.300 align:middle line:90%
you have to do for lifetimes.

00:29:15.300 --> 00:29:19.490 align:middle line:84%
It should not take lifetimes
to experience samadhi, not even

00:29:19.490 --> 00:29:22.040 align:middle line:90%
hours-- minutes.

00:29:22.040 --> 00:29:25.210 align:middle line:84%
And it's just a
question of technique.

00:29:25.210 --> 00:29:28.930 align:middle line:84%
And over the years, you can
trace it throughout history,

00:29:28.930 --> 00:29:32.320 align:middle line:84%
you can watch what happened
with the concepts of meditation,

00:29:32.320 --> 00:29:36.120 align:middle line:84%
became complicated
and misunderstood.

00:29:36.120 --> 00:29:38.810 align:middle line:90%
Transcending is natural.

00:29:38.810 --> 00:29:41.150 align:middle line:90%
We're hardwired for it.

00:29:41.150 --> 00:29:46.830 align:middle line:84%
The brain is as if specifically
designed by someone,

00:29:46.830 --> 00:29:51.340 align:middle line:84%
something, designed to
transcend, to experience

00:29:51.340 --> 00:29:53.340 align:middle line:90%
our universal nature.

00:29:53.340 --> 00:29:56.250 align:middle line:84%
Unfortunately, we don't
access that capability.

00:29:56.250 --> 00:29:57.650 align:middle line:90%
We've got the hardware.

00:29:57.650 --> 00:29:58.680 align:middle line:90%
We don't have the software.

00:29:58.680 --> 00:30:00.530 align:middle line:90%
We don't have the training.

00:30:00.530 --> 00:30:05.040 align:middle line:84%
So the training just involves
quiet, personal instruction.

00:30:05.040 --> 00:30:09.030 align:middle line:84%
And it only takes about an
hour or so for about four days

00:30:09.030 --> 00:30:12.560 align:middle line:84%
in a row to be sure one is
transcending effortlessly.

00:30:12.560 --> 00:30:14.765 align:middle line:84%
And then you've got it
for the rest of your life.

00:30:14.765 --> 00:30:17.570 align:middle line:84%
Because you started
really early.

00:30:17.570 --> 00:30:18.270 align:middle line:90%
How early?

00:30:18.270 --> 00:30:20.280 align:middle line:90%
17 years old, yeah.

00:30:20.280 --> 00:30:22.770 align:middle line:84%
I just happened to
come across-- well,

00:30:22.770 --> 00:30:26.880 align:middle line:84%
I was trying many things, I must
say, at that age, many things.

00:30:26.880 --> 00:30:30.120 align:middle line:84%
And I've since really
dappled and experimented

00:30:30.120 --> 00:30:34.450 align:middle line:84%
with many, many
things and gained

00:30:34.450 --> 00:30:37.860 align:middle line:84%
certain benefits from a
number of different things.

00:30:37.860 --> 00:30:40.140 align:middle line:84%
But what was really
life-changing for me,

00:30:40.140 --> 00:30:42.070 align:middle line:84%
and what is the most
fundamental experience,

00:30:42.070 --> 00:30:47.230 align:middle line:84%
really for anything, is going
beyond the whole mental circus,

00:30:47.230 --> 00:30:51.200 align:middle line:84%
going beyond thought
completely and experiencing

00:30:51.200 --> 00:30:53.680 align:middle line:90%
our core being.

00:30:53.680 --> 00:30:57.430 align:middle line:84%
That is called
samadhi, transcending.

00:30:57.430 --> 00:30:59.890 align:middle line:90%
And that is the essence of it.

00:30:59.890 --> 00:31:01.910 align:middle line:84%
That's where development
really starts.

00:31:01.910 --> 00:31:06.250 align:middle line:84%
That's where the rapid
unfoldment of the brain begins.

00:31:06.250 --> 00:31:10.140 align:middle line:84%
And that's the experience that
needs to be given to children.

00:31:10.140 --> 00:31:12.030 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't have to
have any belief.

00:31:12.030 --> 00:31:13.415 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't have
to have any dogma.

00:31:13.415 --> 00:31:14.390 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't matter.

00:31:14.390 --> 00:31:16.230 align:middle line:90%
It's not an intellectual thing.

00:31:16.230 --> 00:31:17.490 align:middle line:90%
It's not visualizing.

00:31:17.490 --> 00:31:19.250 align:middle line:90%
It's not contemplating.

00:31:19.250 --> 00:31:23.250 align:middle line:84%
It's not dispassionate
self-reflection.

00:31:23.250 --> 00:31:25.220 align:middle line:90%
All of that has to do with mind.

00:31:25.220 --> 00:31:30.201 align:middle line:84%
It's going, slipping
beyond mind to being.

00:31:30.201 --> 00:31:34.550 align:middle line:84%
In that space, when
you say transcendent,

00:31:34.550 --> 00:31:37.390 align:middle line:84%
does it transcend also
the limiting belief

00:31:37.390 --> 00:31:40.240 align:middle line:84%
and what we have in store
in the unconscious mind?

00:31:40.240 --> 00:31:47.830 align:middle line:84%
Absolutely transcends mind,
belief, sensation, feeling,

00:31:47.830 --> 00:31:51.320 align:middle line:90%
intellect, ego-- everything.

00:31:51.320 --> 00:31:54.340 align:middle line:84%
It's a radically
different experience--

00:31:54.340 --> 00:31:58.570 align:middle line:84%
radically different experience--
from anything we experience

00:31:58.570 --> 00:32:00.540 align:middle line:90%
in waking consciousness.

00:32:00.540 --> 00:32:02.390 align:middle line:90%
It's like day and night.

00:32:02.390 --> 00:32:04.800 align:middle line:84%
If you look at the brain,
the brain is normally

00:32:04.800 --> 00:32:07.460 align:middle line:84%
quite chaotic, and this part
of the brain is doing this,

00:32:07.460 --> 00:32:09.110 align:middle line:90%
this part is doing this.

00:32:09.110 --> 00:32:12.880 align:middle line:84%
There's not much integration,
coordination, communication.

00:32:12.880 --> 00:32:17.170 align:middle line:84%
In the state of unbounded
awareness, transcending,

00:32:17.170 --> 00:32:21.440 align:middle line:84%
the entire brain is
absolutely synchronous.

00:32:21.440 --> 00:32:24.220 align:middle line:84%
The awareness
expands to infinity,

00:32:24.220 --> 00:32:26.730 align:middle line:90%
immortality, beyond time.

00:32:26.730 --> 00:32:29.610 align:middle line:90%
It is unmistakable.

00:32:29.610 --> 00:32:35.080 align:middle line:84%
That experience is as simple,
as natural, and more important,

00:32:35.080 --> 00:32:38.720 align:middle line:84%
I think, than any
experience we normally have.

00:32:38.720 --> 00:32:41.010 align:middle line:90%
We're all designed to have it.

00:32:41.010 --> 00:32:43.740 align:middle line:84%
And the tragedy
of education today

00:32:43.740 --> 00:32:46.110 align:middle line:90%
is that it doesn't give it.

00:32:46.110 --> 00:32:49.920 align:middle line:84%
And that's why, with David
Lynch, the filmmaker,

00:32:49.920 --> 00:32:52.060 align:middle line:84%
founded the David
Lynch Foundation

00:32:52.060 --> 00:32:55.800 align:middle line:84%
to bring that experience
to everyone in the world.

00:32:55.800 --> 00:32:57.950 align:middle line:90%
And it's easy to do.

00:32:57.950 --> 00:32:59.390 align:middle line:10%
And also through
movies, I guess,

00:32:59.390 --> 00:33:02.110 align:middle line:10%
that you have put
together with him

00:33:02.110 --> 00:33:05.630 align:middle line:10%
to be able to see it and witness
it and even experience it

00:33:05.630 --> 00:33:07.685 align:middle line:10%
without having maybe the tools?

00:33:07.685 --> 00:33:08.710 align:middle line:90%
That's an interesting point.

00:33:08.710 --> 00:33:11.660 align:middle line:84%
There have been some
films about meditation,

00:33:11.660 --> 00:33:17.030 align:middle line:84%
films like "The Secret,"
films like "What the Bleep."

00:33:17.030 --> 00:33:19.280 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, I've
been in those films.

00:33:19.280 --> 00:33:23.360 align:middle line:84%
But David himself
hasn't really made films

00:33:23.360 --> 00:33:25.880 align:middle line:84%
about the transcendent,
interestingly, even though he

00:33:25.880 --> 00:33:29.960 align:middle line:84%
himself is a very deep,
regular meditator.

00:33:29.960 --> 00:33:33.130 align:middle line:84%
For him, his joy
of filmmaking is

00:33:33.130 --> 00:33:36.960 align:middle line:84%
different-- a little bizarre,
but also very fascinating.

00:33:36.960 --> 00:33:40.130 align:middle line:84%
He's a creative artist,
absolutely the real thing.

00:33:40.130 --> 00:33:43.010 align:middle line:84%
He's an incredible,
creative artist.

00:33:43.010 --> 00:33:45.840 align:middle line:84%
But his interest in
the transcendent,

00:33:45.840 --> 00:33:50.170 align:middle line:84%
he hasn't yet used film to
kind of expose or reveal that.

00:33:50.170 --> 00:33:51.790 align:middle line:90%
Maybe someday he will.

00:33:51.790 --> 00:33:55.330 align:middle line:84%
So his work with his foundation
is really to bring the funding

00:33:55.330 --> 00:34:00.640 align:middle line:84%
so that schools can actually
hire the type of education

00:34:00.640 --> 00:34:03.260 align:middle line:84%
of transcendental
meditation instructor

00:34:03.260 --> 00:34:06.520 align:middle line:84%
that can easily give that
experience to all the children.

00:34:06.520 --> 00:34:08.210 align:middle line:84%
And that's one of
the things I've been

00:34:08.210 --> 00:34:10.360 align:middle line:90%
very happy to be involved with.

00:34:10.360 --> 00:34:14.889 align:middle line:84%
Tell us on the neuroscience
level and the neuroplasticity,

00:34:14.889 --> 00:34:17.949 align:middle line:84%
how does that rewire
even our brains?

00:34:17.949 --> 00:34:21.706 align:middle line:90%
That is a really good question.

00:34:21.706 --> 00:34:26.070 align:middle line:84%
You know, experience, any
experience, changes the brain.

00:34:26.070 --> 00:34:31.199 align:middle line:84%
Our brains are amazingly
flexible and changeable,

00:34:31.199 --> 00:34:32.380 align:middle line:90%
incredibly plastic.

00:34:32.380 --> 00:34:34.510 align:middle line:84%
We're always forging
new connections,

00:34:34.510 --> 00:34:36.960 align:middle line:90%
creating new neural pathways.

00:34:36.960 --> 00:34:39.550 align:middle line:84%
And, of course,
any new experience,

00:34:39.550 --> 00:34:42.650 align:middle line:84%
any fundamental experience
like transcending,

00:34:42.650 --> 00:34:46.250 align:middle line:84%
is going to start
to rewire the brain.

00:34:46.250 --> 00:34:50.630 align:middle line:84%
Now, during transcending,
two things happen.

00:34:50.630 --> 00:34:54.389 align:middle line:84%
Firstly, the higher brain,
the prefrontal cortex,

00:34:54.389 --> 00:34:56.690 align:middle line:84%
the executive
center of the brain,

00:34:56.690 --> 00:34:58.670 align:middle line:90%
gets directly stimulated.

00:34:58.670 --> 00:35:01.240 align:middle line:90%
It lights up.

00:35:01.240 --> 00:35:03.980 align:middle line:84%
And that's important,
because the higher brain

00:35:03.980 --> 00:35:07.800 align:middle line:84%
is responsible for all of
our higher human functions,

00:35:07.800 --> 00:35:09.850 align:middle line:84%
moral reasoning,
judgment, planning,

00:35:09.850 --> 00:35:13.660 align:middle line:90%
decision making, all of that.

00:35:13.660 --> 00:35:19.390 align:middle line:84%
It sits over the primitive
brain and maintains control.

00:35:19.390 --> 00:35:23.010 align:middle line:84%
It's our rational filter
against primitive, impulsive,

00:35:23.010 --> 00:35:25.330 align:middle line:90%
aggressive, violent behavior.

00:35:25.330 --> 00:35:31.110 align:middle line:84%
But under stress, the
prefrontal cortex shuts down.

00:35:31.110 --> 00:35:34.910 align:middle line:84%
Under chronic stress, which
pervades the world today,

00:35:34.910 --> 00:35:38.050 align:middle line:84%
the higher brain shuts
down chronically and even

00:35:38.050 --> 00:35:40.090 align:middle line:90%
fails to develop properly.

00:35:40.090 --> 00:35:43.580 align:middle line:10%
So we end up in a world, living
in a world where so many people

00:35:43.580 --> 00:35:47.720 align:middle line:10%
are walking around with an
underdeveloped higher brain,

00:35:47.720 --> 00:35:50.140 align:middle line:10%
kind of an adolescent world.

00:35:50.140 --> 00:35:52.340 align:middle line:84%
And if you look
at the television

00:35:52.340 --> 00:35:54.420 align:middle line:84%
or what's going on
the news, you'll

00:35:54.420 --> 00:35:57.810 align:middle line:84%
agree that we're living very
much in an adolescent world

00:35:57.810 --> 00:36:00.840 align:middle line:84%
of aggression and impulsive
behavior, violence

00:36:00.840 --> 00:36:04.570 align:middle line:84%
and nationalism and
narrow-minded, self centered

00:36:04.570 --> 00:36:07.630 align:middle line:90%
shortsightedness and so on.

00:36:07.630 --> 00:36:11.080 align:middle line:84%
So we need to develop
the higher brain.

00:36:11.080 --> 00:36:13.570 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, transcending
lights up the higher brain.

00:36:13.570 --> 00:36:17.440 align:middle line:84%
But more importantly, it
integrates the higher brain

00:36:17.440 --> 00:36:20.440 align:middle line:84%
with the rest of the brain
so that the higher brain

00:36:20.440 --> 00:36:25.710 align:middle line:84%
can do its job, which is
to control the entire brain

00:36:25.710 --> 00:36:27.790 align:middle line:90%
so we're not driven by impulse.

00:36:27.790 --> 00:36:30.920 align:middle line:84%
We're not driven by
primitive impulses.

00:36:30.920 --> 00:36:34.750 align:middle line:84%
We're driven by our loftiest,
highest aspirations.

00:36:34.750 --> 00:36:37.980 align:middle line:84%
So, yes, it completely
rewires the brain,

00:36:37.980 --> 00:36:41.000 align:middle line:84%
not just during meditation,
which you see it so striking.

00:36:41.000 --> 00:36:43.300 align:middle line:84%
It's amazing to
see the difference

00:36:43.300 --> 00:36:46.310 align:middle line:84%
between the meditating
brain, the EEG

00:36:46.310 --> 00:36:49.900 align:middle line:84%
of the meditating brain, and
the EEG of the waking brain.

00:36:49.900 --> 00:36:53.410 align:middle line:84%
But over time, that
orderly brain functioning,

00:36:53.410 --> 00:36:56.460 align:middle line:84%
synchronous brain functioning,
coherent brain functioning,

00:36:56.460 --> 00:36:58.300 align:middle line:90%
becomes permanent.

00:36:58.300 --> 00:37:02.690 align:middle line:84%
And when it becomes permanent,
it is called enlightenment.

00:37:02.690 --> 00:37:07.760 align:middle line:84%
And enlightenment is
really, fundamentally just

00:37:07.760 --> 00:37:12.350 align:middle line:84%
as a definition, it's when
our unbounded, immortal, inner

00:37:12.350 --> 00:37:16.460 align:middle line:84%
self, when our own pure
consciousness becomes

00:37:16.460 --> 00:37:21.230 align:middle line:84%
permanently established so
that in dynamic activity, even

00:37:21.230 --> 00:37:25.150 align:middle line:84%
during deep sleep,
we are never lost

00:37:25.150 --> 00:37:29.940 align:middle line:84%
to the experience of our
unbounded, immortal, blissful

00:37:29.940 --> 00:37:31.050 align:middle line:90%
self.

00:37:31.050 --> 00:37:35.180 align:middle line:84%
It's permanent samadhi in the
midst of dynamic activity.

00:37:35.180 --> 00:37:36.990 align:middle line:90%
That's proper brain functioning.

00:37:36.990 --> 00:37:39.860 align:middle line:84%
That's how our brains
were designed to work.

00:37:39.860 --> 00:37:43.470 align:middle line:84%
But it just takes--
like speech is natural.

00:37:43.470 --> 00:37:45.430 align:middle line:90%
We're designed to talk.

