That's his business.

00:46:02.230 --> 00:46:04.850 align:middle line:84%
So not everybody
understands it, of course.

00:46:04.850 --> 00:46:06.876 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, I'd
have to say, you

00:46:06.876 --> 00:46:12.600 align:middle line:84%
know, to really understand it
takes some degree of experience

00:46:12.600 --> 00:46:13.820 align:middle line:90%
with it.

00:46:13.820 --> 00:46:16.410 align:middle line:84%
When you talk about group
meditation, for example,

00:46:16.410 --> 00:46:20.840 align:middle line:84%
reducing crime, preventing
war, reducing social stress

00:46:20.840 --> 00:46:25.440 align:middle line:84%
and promoting social harmony,
that's hard for many people.

00:46:25.440 --> 00:46:28.450 align:middle line:84%
It's hard for a physical
scientist to understand.

00:46:28.450 --> 00:46:31.340 align:middle line:84%
I think for many physical
scientists, consciousness

00:46:31.340 --> 00:46:37.180 align:middle line:84%
either doesn't exist, or it's
some superficial byproduct

00:46:37.180 --> 00:46:40.200 align:middle line:84%
of the electrochemical
processes of the brain,

00:46:40.200 --> 00:46:42.480 align:middle line:90%
something superficial.

00:46:42.480 --> 00:46:45.170 align:middle line:84%
What we're talking about
here is consciousness

00:46:45.170 --> 00:46:50.160 align:middle line:84%
as fundamental, consciousness
as the unified field.

00:46:50.160 --> 00:46:53.250 align:middle line:84%
Now, physicists who are really
active in the field, they

00:46:53.250 --> 00:46:57.270 align:middle line:84%
accept the unified field,
the fundamental unity,

00:46:57.270 --> 00:47:00.190 align:middle line:84%
the basis of the surface
diversity of the world.

00:47:00.190 --> 00:47:03.710 align:middle line:84%
If you ask them, is
that fundamental unity

00:47:03.710 --> 00:47:06.770 align:middle line:90%
of life consciousness?

00:47:06.770 --> 00:47:07.660 align:middle line:90%
they'd say, what?

00:47:07.660 --> 00:47:11.660 align:middle line:84%
I don't think so, but,
honestly, I've never

00:47:11.660 --> 00:47:13.820 align:middle line:90%
thought about consciousness.

00:47:13.820 --> 00:47:17.040 align:middle line:84%
Those few physicists who do
think about consciousness,

00:47:17.040 --> 00:47:20.420 align:middle line:84%
including some at the
conference in Doorn here,

00:47:20.420 --> 00:47:24.610 align:middle line:84%
like Menas Kafatos,
they understand

00:47:24.610 --> 00:47:26.610 align:middle line:84%
that the unified field
is consciousness.

00:47:26.610 --> 00:47:29.040 align:middle line:84%
But honestly, most physicists
don't think about it.

00:47:29.040 --> 00:47:30.120 align:middle line:90%
It's not their business.

00:47:30.120 --> 00:47:32.330 align:middle line:84%
They're not into the
business of consciousness.

00:47:32.330 --> 00:47:35.820 align:middle line:84%
Leave that to the psychiatrists
and psychologists.

00:47:35.820 --> 00:47:38.190 align:middle line:84%
They're into the
business of physics,

00:47:38.190 --> 00:47:42.580 align:middle line:84%
and they don't yet
see the unity of the

00:47:42.580 --> 00:47:45.290 align:middle line:90%
objective and subjective world.

00:47:45.290 --> 00:47:47.080 align:middle line:84%
So there's a
relatively few people

00:47:47.080 --> 00:47:50.220 align:middle line:84%
in the world who are experts
in unified field theory.

00:47:50.220 --> 00:47:52.790 align:middle line:84%
There are relatively few experts
in the world who are experts

00:47:52.790 --> 00:47:56.540 align:middle line:84%
in consciousness and
unfortunately, very few people

00:47:56.540 --> 00:48:00.200 align:middle line:84%
in the world who are really
experts in both and that

00:48:00.200 --> 00:48:03.220 align:middle line:84%
are capable of creating
the connections

00:48:03.220 --> 00:48:06.810 align:middle line:84%
between deep consciousness
and deep physics.

00:48:06.810 --> 00:48:10.170 align:middle line:84%
And it's a fun,
fascinating, wonderful world

00:48:10.170 --> 00:48:11.660 align:middle line:90%
in which to play.

00:48:11.660 --> 00:48:13.300 align:middle line:84%
But there are very few
people to play with.

00:48:13.300 --> 00:48:14.350 align:middle line:90%
Mhm, mhm.

00:48:14.350 --> 00:48:16.515 align:middle line:10%
Well, we can definitely
feel through this interview

00:48:16.515 --> 00:48:18.690 align:middle line:10%
that you have those both sides.

00:48:18.690 --> 00:48:22.330 align:middle line:84%
And would you attribute
that to the meditation,

00:48:22.330 --> 00:48:25.590 align:middle line:84%
that it has developed
each of the side together?

00:48:25.590 --> 00:48:27.270 align:middle line:90%
And are those now linked?

00:48:27.270 --> 00:48:28.840 align:middle line:90%
That's interesting.

00:48:28.840 --> 00:48:30.440 align:middle line:84%
Well, it is
certainly true for me

00:48:30.440 --> 00:48:33.880 align:middle line:84%
that my meditation
has really enhanced

00:48:33.880 --> 00:48:36.660 align:middle line:90%
my ability to do physics.

00:48:36.660 --> 00:48:39.180 align:middle line:84%
I started to meditate at
the same time I was starting

00:48:39.180 --> 00:48:41.780 align:middle line:84%
to learn quantum mechanics, and
I was finding quantum mechanics

00:48:41.780 --> 00:48:45.510 align:middle line:84%
very abstract and really
very difficult and dry,

00:48:45.510 --> 00:48:48.820 align:middle line:90%
dry meaning kind of boring.

00:48:48.820 --> 00:48:51.920 align:middle line:84%
But, you know, after
meditation, it's like, wow,

00:48:51.920 --> 00:48:56.170 align:middle line:84%
these ideas are just
lucid and exciting

00:48:56.170 --> 00:48:58.700 align:middle line:90%
and profound and wonderful.

00:48:58.700 --> 00:49:01.240 align:middle line:84%
So it really
awakened my interest

00:49:01.240 --> 00:49:02.390 align:middle line:90%
and ability to do physics.

00:49:02.390 --> 00:49:04.050 align:middle line:84%
And other meditating
scientists will

00:49:04.050 --> 00:49:06.080 align:middle line:90%
say exactly the same thing.

00:49:06.080 --> 00:49:09.440 align:middle line:84%
So I think for me, meditation
was very important to develop

00:49:09.440 --> 00:49:10.530 align:middle line:90%
as a physicist.

00:49:10.530 --> 00:49:14.660 align:middle line:84%
One of my award-winning series,
the so-called Supersymmetric

00:49:14.660 --> 00:49:18.260 align:middle line:84%
Flipped SU(5) Grand
Unified Field Theory,

00:49:18.260 --> 00:49:22.630 align:middle line:84%
was completely
derived in meditation.

00:49:22.630 --> 00:49:25.090 align:middle line:84%
So it's been an
important tool for me.

00:49:25.090 --> 00:49:27.280 align:middle line:90%
But I don't know.

00:49:27.280 --> 00:49:32.470 align:middle line:84%
I've always believed
that truth is one

00:49:32.470 --> 00:49:36.080 align:middle line:84%
and that if physics brings
truth, which it does--

00:49:36.080 --> 00:49:39.040 align:middle line:84%
it's reliable; it's
testable; it's true--

00:49:39.040 --> 00:49:43.570 align:middle line:84%
and if the deep spiritual,
even religious, traditions

00:49:43.570 --> 00:49:48.000 align:middle line:84%
of the world bring truth, and
they do, or they wouldn't have

00:49:48.000 --> 00:49:53.190 align:middle line:84%
survived for millennia as a
useful, true guide to life,

00:49:53.190 --> 00:49:56.970 align:middle line:84%
then those two truths
must be linked.

00:49:56.970 --> 00:49:58.990 align:middle line:84%
Because there ultimately
is only one truth.

00:49:58.990 --> 00:50:02.090 align:middle line:84%
And where those two
truths come together,

00:50:02.090 --> 00:50:05.310 align:middle line:84%
the truth of the subjective
world and the truth

00:50:05.310 --> 00:50:07.870 align:middle line:84%
of the objective world
of modern science,

00:50:07.870 --> 00:50:11.280 align:middle line:84%
is at the level of
the unified field.

00:50:11.280 --> 00:50:13.960 align:middle line:84%
And that is where
pure consciousness

00:50:13.960 --> 00:50:18.880 align:middle line:84%
and pure existence,
the source of thought

00:50:18.880 --> 00:50:22.910 align:middle line:84%
and the source of the
objective world, come together.

00:50:22.910 --> 00:50:27.500 align:middle line:84%
There's an old saying,
atman is Brahman.

00:50:27.500 --> 00:50:31.730 align:middle line:84%
Brahman is the
fundamental unity of life.

00:50:31.730 --> 00:50:34.030 align:middle line:84%
Atman is our
consciousness, the self.

00:50:34.030 --> 00:50:38.250 align:middle line:84%
That self, pure consciousness,
the meditative state, samadhi,

00:50:38.250 --> 00:50:45.601 align:middle line:84%
is Brahman, is the experience
of the universal truth of unity.

00:50:45.601 --> 00:50:46.300 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:50:46.300 --> 00:50:48.940 align:middle line:84%
Thank you, John, so
much for this moment

00:50:48.940 --> 00:50:50.580 align:middle line:90%
and for this interview.

00:50:50.580 --> 00:50:52.710 align:middle line:84%
And I look forward to
seeing you and hearing

00:50:52.710 --> 00:50:54.550 align:middle line:84%
you speak at the
conference here in Holland.

00:50:54.550 --> 00:50:55.440 align:middle line:90%
Thank you very much.

00:50:55.440 --> 00:50:57.680 align:middle line:84%
It's a great pleasure,
Lilou, and really

00:50:57.680 --> 00:50:59.880 align:middle line:84%
great pleasure to speak to
your wonderful audience.

00:50:59.880 --> 00:51:00.750 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:51:00.750 --> 00:51:03.530 align:middle line:84%
Thank you, beautiful
Gaiam TV co-creators.

00:51:03.530 --> 00:51:05.170 align:middle line:90%
Much love from Holland.

